Collaborated with internal stakeholders to implement new processes to address and support unit’s non-standard, niche area of expertise. Supported CEO and Global COO on budget reporting and analysis. Managed global risk reporting and developed mitigation strategy to decrease or eliminate exposure.

member_experience_collection.description: Taught upper-class journalism students introduction to digital editing software (Final Cut, Protools), on-camera reporting, analyzing vocal pronunciation and quality (using IPA annotation and Fitzmaurice Vocal Technique), and approach to developing various news packages. member_experience_collection.title: Analyst, Business services
member_experience_collection.description: Supported Chairman and CEO on marketing strategy, built high-level dashboards and CRM forecasting capabilities using Salesforce for C-Suite consumption at 10EQS, a global management consulting start-up founded by ex-McKinsey directors. Designed presentations and developed content for client engagements on behalf of senior consultants. Edited demo videos, and drafted best-practice documents for the operations team. Designed marketing materials for external conferences and events. Served as a the SalesForce administrator for the sales team in North America. Served as project manager for 10EQS’ real-estate acquisition initiative that relocated corporate headquarters resulting in ~$100K reduction in general operating expense per year from 2013 to 2015.
